Kate Middleton is pregnant again
Fashion icon and Duchess of Cambridge Kate Middleton is pregnant again. The official Twitter of the   announced early this morning that Prince William and Kate Middleton are expecting their second child. The Duke and Duchess of Cambridge are very pleased to announce that The Duchess of Cambridge is expecting their second child 
 
 The announcement, it seems, needed to be made, as Middleton is being treated for "Hyperemesis Gravidarum,"  . Hyperemesis Gravidarum is also known as acute morning sickness. Middleton was also hospitalized with morning sickness, including dehydration, nausea, and vomiting, during her first pregnancy.  A royal baby, especially one of such prominence, always receives heaps of attention. The future baby will be fourth in line to the throne following his grandfather Prince Charles, his father Prince William, and his 1-year-old brother.  has, of course, already begun, with the names Henry, Elizabeth, and Victoria leading the pack.  No details have been given yet on the potential due date of the baby, but   that Middleton is not yet past the 12 week mark. The expected month of the birth will be announced once Middleton is safely past the 12-week mark. Get our newsletter in your inbox twice a week. 